<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Loan Agreement - Satin Finserv Limited</title>
  <style>
    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 0;
    }

    html, body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      background-color: #ffffff;
      font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;
      -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;
    }

    .page {
      position: relative;
      width: 210mm;
      min-height: 297mm;
      padding: 18mm 18mm 18mm 18mm;
      box-sizing: border-box;
      page-break-after: always;
      overflow: hidden;
      color: #000000;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .page:last-child {
      page-break-after: avoid;
    }

    .doc-title {
      font-size: 12pt;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    p {
      font-size: 10.5pt;
      line-height: 1.5;
      text-align: justify;
      margin: 0 0 12px 0;
    }

    .section-heading {
      font-size: 11pt;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin: 16px 0 10px 0;
    }

    /* Clause layout: number in left column, text in right */
    .clause {
      display: flex;
      margin-bottom: 11px;
    }

    .clause .num {
      flex: 0 0 42px;
      font-size: 10.5pt;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    .clause .num.wide {
      flex: 0 0 58px;
    }

    .clause .txt {
      flex: 1;
      font-size: 10.5pt;
      line-height: 1.5;
      text-align: justify;
    }

    .clause .txt p {
      margin: 0 0 8px 0;
    }

    .indent-1 {
      margin-left: 42px;
    }

    .indent-2 {
      margin-left: 84px;
    }

    b { font-weight: bold; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <%
    const safeBorrowerName = typeof borrowerName !== 'undefined' ? borrowerName : 'the Borrower';
    const safeLoanAmount = typeof loanAmount !== 'undefined' ? loanAmount : '';
  %>

  <!-- ================= PAGE 1 ================= -->
  <div class="page">
    <div class="doc-title">LOAN AGREEMENT</div>

    <p>This Loan Agreement (<b>"Agreement"</b>) is made at the place and date as mentioned in Schedule 1 hereto:</p>

    <p><b>BETWEEN</b></p>

    <p><b>The Persons</b> set out in Schedule 1 (hereinafter referred to as the <b>"Borrower"</b>);</p>

    <p><b>AND</b></p>

    <p><b>SATIN FINSERV LIMITED</b>, a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013 with CIN
      U65999HR2018PLC099128, registered with the Reserve Bank of India as a non-banking financial company and having its
      registered office at Registered Office and its Corporate Office at 4th Floor, B wing, Plot No. 492 Udyog Vihar, Phase III
      Gurugram Haryana 122016 (hereinafter referred to as <b>"Lender"</b> or <b>"SFL"</b> which expression shall unless
      repugnant to the context or meaning thereof be deemed to include its successors and assigns).</p>

    <p><b>WHEREAS</b>:</p>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">A.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower has approached and requested the Lender to provide certain financial assistance for the purpose of acquisition of a commercial vehicle (the <b>"Purpose"</b>).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">B.</div>
      <div class="txt">Accordingly, the Lender has agreed to provide to the Borrower financial assistance in the form of an Indian rupee denominated vehicle loan facility (<b>"Loan Facility"</b>) up to a maximum principal amount set out in Schedule 1 in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">C.</div>
      <div class="txt">Pursuant to the request of the Borrower along with the Co-Borrower, the Lender has agreed to grant the Loan Facility to the Borrower upon the terms and conditions as set out in this Agreement.</div>
    </div>

    <p><b>NOW THIS AGREEMENT WITHNESSETH AS UNDER:</b></p>

    <div class="section-heading">1. DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION</div>

    <p>Any reference in this Agreement to:</p>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">any <b>"document"</b> or <b>"agreement"</b> includes that document or agreement as amended, supplemented, restated and/or replaced from time to time;</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">a <b>"person"</b> includes any individual, company, corporation, a Hindu Undivided Family, unincorporated association or body (including a partnership, limited liability partnership, trust, joint venture, proprietorship, society or consortium) (whether or not registered and whether or not having a separate legal personality), government, state, agency, organization or other entity whether or not having separate legal personality, and its and any subsequent successors in title, heirs, permitted transferees and permitted assigns, in each case in accordance with their respective interests;</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.3.</div>
      <div class="txt"><b>"Lender"</b> shall be construed so as to include its successors in interest, assigns and transferees.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.4.</div>
      <div class="txt"><b>"Applicant"</b> means any person who has applied for the Loan Facility, whether individually or jointly, including any proposed Borrower or Co-Borrower. The Applicant and the Borrower may be the same person or different persons. References to the Applicant shall, where the context requires, include the Borrower, and references to the Borrower shall include the Applicant to the extent such person has executed or is bound by the relevant Finance Documents.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.5.</div>
      <div class="txt"><b>"Borrower"</b> includes "Co-Borrower/s".</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ================= PAGE 2 ================= -->
  <div class="page">
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.7.</div>
      <div class="txt"><b>"Availability Period"</b> means the period commencing on the date of execution of this Agreement (or such other date as specified in the Sanction Letter) and ending on the earlier of (a) the Final Availability Date specified in the Sanction Letter, or (b) the date on which the Facility is fully drawn or cancelled.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.8.</div>
      <div class="txt"><b>"Business day"</b> means a day (other than a Saturday, Sunday or a bank holiday) on which banks are open for general business in Delhi.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.9.</div>
      <div class="txt"><b>"Finance Documents"</b> shall mean this Agreement along with its schedules and annexures, the sanction letter and any other documents related to the loan application of the Borrower.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.10.</div>
      <div class="txt"><b>"Outstanding Obligations"</b> shall mean all obligations of the Borrower to pay, repay or reimburse, as the case may be, the principal amounts of the Loan Facility, interest, default charges, break costs, bounce charges, additional interest, prepayment premium, all costs and charges and other monies owed by, and all other present and future obligations and liabilities of the Borrower to the Lender under this Agreement and the Finance Documents, all costs, charges and expenses including but not limited to the legal expenses and costs of preserving the securities or enforcement thereof, incurred by the Lender under the Finance Documents.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.11.</div>
      <div class="txt"><b>"Registration Certificate"</b> shall mean the certificate of registration of the Vehicle or any such similar document with different nomenclature issued by the applicable government authority with which the Vehicle is registered under the Applicable Law.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.12.</div>
      <div class="txt"><b>"Vehicle"</b> or <b>"Hypothecated Vehicle"</b> shall mean the new vehicles to be acquired by the Borrower in respect of which the Loan is granted/to be granted hereunder including any accessories, if any.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.13.</div>
      <div class="txt">Words denoting the singular will include the plural and vice versa.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.14.</div>
      <div class="txt">Words denoting gender shall include masculine or feminine or neuter gender as applicable, such that "it/its" shall refer to "he/his" or "she/her" and vice versa, as applicable.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.15.</div>
      <div class="txt">Headings to Clauses and Schedules are for ease of reference only.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.16.</div>
      <div class="txt">References to "Clauses" and "Schedules" are to clauses of and schedules to this Agreement, and references to this Agreement include its Schedules.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.17.</div>
      <div class="txt">Unless otherwise specified, whenever any payment to be made or action to be taken under this Agreement, is required to be made or taken on a day other than a Business Day, such payment shall be made or action shall be taken on the immediately succeeding Business Day, except if such due date is for the payment of principal and accrued interest, in which case the payment to be made on such due date (including accrued interest) shall be made on the immediately preceding Business Day. Interest and any other amounts payable pursuant to this Agreement will be determined on the basis of a year consisting of 365 (three hundred and sixty five) days, and the same shall be paid by the Borrower monthly along with the EMI's.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.18.</div>
      <div class="txt">Where any provision of any Finance Document requires any determination to be made, whether for adequacy of or any requirement for any action taken or to be taken by any party, a conclusion to be arrived at, a decision to be made, an opinion to be formed, or where there is a possibility of or the occurrence of a disagreement, dispute, conflict of interpretation between the parties in relation to any provision of any Finance Document, or any other such assessment to be made, the determination or conclusion or opinion or decision or interpretation or assessment of the Lender shall be final and binding.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.19.</div>
      <div class="txt">Any consent, permission, waiver, approval or clearance required to be provided by the Lender shall mean the prior written consent of the Lender.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.20.</div>
      <div class="txt">A Default is "continuing" or "outstanding" if it has not been remedied or waived in writing.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">1.21.</div>
      <div class="txt">All references to the knowledge, information, belief or awareness of any person shall be deemed to include the</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ================= PAGE 3 ================= -->
  <div class="page">
    <p>its sole discretion, at any time cancel all or any part of the Loan Facility which has not been utilized.</p>

    <div class="section-heading">3. DRAWDOWN OF THE FACILITY</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">3.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower agrees that all proceeds under this Loan Facility shall be disbursed directly to the Vehicle dealer, as a lump-sum or in suitable installments in the specified account of the Vehicle dealer, details of which are set out in Schedule 1 (<b>"Loan Facility Account"</b>). The Borrower further agrees and undertakes that such disbursement to the Vehicle dealer shall be deemed to be a disbursement to the Borrower.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">3.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Loan Facility may be availed in a single drawdown or multiple tranches, as agreed prior to the first disbursement and with the explicit consent of the Lender.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">3.3.</div>
      <div class="txt">Upon the Borrower complying with the conditions of this Agreement and such other conditions as may be prescribed by the Lender, the Lender may permit the Borrower to utilize the Loan Facility solely for the Purpose.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">3.4.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Loan Facility shall be disbursed only within the "Availability Period" and in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement. The "Availability Period" would be explicitly defined in advance by the Lender and can be amended by the Lender at any point in time, during the tenor of the loan, for either single or multiple tranche disbursal mode(s).</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-heading">4. CONDITIONS PRECEDENT</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">4.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">Prior to the disbursement of the Loan Facility by the Lender, the Borrower shall not be in breach of any terms of this Agreement and shall comply with all requirements mentioned in this Agreement and all other Finance Documents to ensure that this Agreement and the Finance Documents are legally binding and enforceable against the Borrower.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">4.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">Notwithstanding the generality of the foregoing, before disbursing the Loan Facility under this Agreement, the Borrower shall provide to the Lender all documents, undertakings and evidence, and comply with all conditions precedent (including but not limited to completion of all "know your customer" checks) as may be required by the Lender to the satisfaction of the Lender (<b>"Conditions Precedent"</b>) unless otherwise specifically waived by the Lender in writing.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">4.3.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower confirms that the Borrower is a citizen and permanent resident of India (in case of an individual) and subject to the tax regime of India. The Borrower hereby declares and confirms that the Borrower is not a "Politically Exposed Person" (PEP) or related to any such person, as defined under applicable KYC/AML guidelines issued by the Reserve Bank of India.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-heading">5. REPAYMENT AND PREPAYMENT</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">5.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Loan Facility will be repaid in accordance with the terms set out in Schedule 1, or as otherwise mutually agreed between the Parties in writing.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">5.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">To repay the Loan Facility, the Borrower shall service such account of the Lender as may be communicated by the Lender to the Borrower from time to time, on the respective Due Dates by making repayment of the total principal amount and/or such instalments as set out in Schedule 1 together with any interest, Default Charges, Prepayment Premium (if applicable), Break Costs (if applicable) and commission thereon and all other costs, charges, payments and expenses payable under the Finance Documents and incidental to the Loan Facility disbursed by the Lender to the Borrower under this Agreement. Any amounts due and payable by the Borrower shall be appropriated in the following order unless the Lender in its sole discretion decides otherwise:</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">5.2.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">firstly, towards costs, charges, expenses payable under the Finance Documents;</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">5.2.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">secondly, towards Fees and taxes on fees payable to Lender as per the Finance Documents;</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ================= PAGE 4 ================= -->
  <div class="page">
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">5.4.</div>
      <div class="txt">All payments to be made by the Borrower to the Lender under this Agreement or the Finance Documents shall be made by Cheques/Post Dated Cheques (PDCs)/Electronic Instructions/SI/ECS/ACH or any other mode or instrument permitted by the Lender, in favor of the Lender. In case of any payment towards the dues if made by security cheques submitted by the Borrower to the Lender, then such payment shall be deemed to be received upon that amount being credited to the bank account of the Lender and the Borrower shall be responsible to replace the said security cheque used to make the payment, with a fresh/new security cheque if required by the Lender.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">5.5.</div>
      <div class="txt">Any dispute being raised will not enable the Borrower to withhold payment of any installment.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-heading">6. INTEREST, FEES, COMMISSION, COSTS</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">6.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">The rate of interest on the Loan Facility for the Interest Period is the Interest Rate set out in Schedule 1. The Borrower shall pay accrued interest on the amount disbursed as the Loan Facility on the Interest Payment Dates.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">6.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower will pay all fees, commission, interest, legal fees, and other costs (including in relation to the stamp duty payable on the Finance Documents) and charges in respect of the Loan Facility on the relevant Due Dates.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">6.3.</div>
      <div class="txt">Borrower(s) shall pay any charge, sum levied on the account due to dishonour of any repayment instructions including the dishonour/bounce charges mentioned in Schedule 1. Borrower(s) shall pay any charge, sum, cost, which the Lender would reasonably incur pursuant to enforcing demand of dues, enforcement on breach of this Agreement/Finance Documents or on initiation of any recovery proceedings.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">6.4.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower(s) confirm, agree and undertake as follows: (i) The Borrower(s) has fully understood the mode and manner of computation of the Rate of Interest as more particularly mentioned in the Schedule 1 to this Agreement. (ii) The Borrower(s) will be charged the interest on a monthly basis and the same will be payable on monthly basis along with the EMI's.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-heading">7. DEFAULT CHARGES</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">7.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">In case of occurrence of an Event of Default, without prejudice to any rights of the Lender under the Finance Documents and Applicable Law, the Borrower shall pay Default Charges as set out in Schedule 1. Such charges will accrue on a daily basis from the date of the occurrence of the Event of Default until such Event of Default is cured to the satisfaction of the Lender, or the date of actual payment by the Borrower to the Lender of all Outstanding Obligations (<b>"Default Charges"</b>).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num">7.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower acknowledges that the payment of Default Charges will not absolve the Borrower of any other obligations under the Finance Documents, including making timely payments and providing the requisite documents/undertakings/reports as required under this Agreement or any other Finance Document or affect any of the other rights of the Lender under the Finance Documents. For avoidance of doubt, it is clarified that the payment of Default Charges is in addition to other rights that the Lender has under the Finance Documents, and the Lender reserves all of its rights under this Agreement, the Finance Documents and Applicable Law.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-heading">8. STAMP DUTY</div>

    <p>The Borrower shall promptly pay, and in any case within 10 (ten) Business Days of demand made by the Lender, and shall
      indemnify the Lender against any cost, loss or liability incurred by the Lender in relation to all stamp duty, registration
      and other similar amounts payable in respect of this Agreement or any Finance Document, or for any claims, penalties,
      demands, actions or suits arising out of or relating to any breach of this clause by the Borrower. The Borrower understands
      and agrees that the foregoing includes any stamp duty payable or which may become payable under Applicable Law on this
      Agreement and the other Finance Documents, including pursuant to persons other than the Lender becoming a party to the
      Finance Documents.</p>

    <div class="section-heading">9. CANCELLATION</div>
  </div>

  <!-- ================= PAGE 5 ================= -->
  <div class="page">
    <p>to repay the Outstanding Obligations.</p>

    <div class="section-heading">10. REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">10.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower and the Co-Borrower hereby jointly and severally represent and warrant that each of them: (i) is an individual, or a sole proprietorship, partnership, LLP, company or other entity, as applicable, duly constituted or established and validly existing under applicable law, and competent to contract and capable of entering into and performing obligations under this Agreement and the Finance Documents; and (ii) has all necessary authority and has taken all actions required to execute this Agreement and the Finance Documents and to perform their respective obligations hereunder.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">10.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower hereby represents and warrants that: (i) no encumbrance or lien of any nature whatsoever exists over the Vehicle to be hypothecated in favour of the Lender and the Borrower has obtained all consents and approvals required to avail of the Loan Facility and create security by way of hypothecation of the Vehicle in favour of the Lender; (ii) the Borrower has obtained and done all that is necessary to give full force and effect to this Agreement and the transactions contemplated hereunder, including obtaining all required authorisations, approvals, consents, no-objections, licenses and permissions under applicable law; and (iii) the Borrower has paid all taxes and dues payable to any governmental or local authority and there are no arrears outstanding as on the date hereof.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">10.3.</div>
      <div class="txt">The representations and warranties in this Clause shall be deemed to be repeated until full repayment of all dues to the satisfaction of the Lender.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-heading">11. INDEMNITY AND LIMITATION OF LIABILITY</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">11.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower and the Co-Borrower hereby jointly and severally agree and undertake to indemnify and keep indemnified and hold harmless the Lender and its nominee(s) or any of them and each of their affiliates, officers, directors, employees and advisors and every receiver, attorney, manager, agent or other person appointed by the Lender (each an "Indemnified Party") against any and all actual losses, expenses, liabilities, obligations, damages, actions, proceedings, claims, demands and judgments (including without limitation, legal and other fees on a full indemnity basis) incurred by any Indemnified Party upon the breach of any provisions of this Agreement or any other Finance Documents on the part of the Borrower herein contained and against all demands, actions, suits or proceedings made, filed, instituted against the Lender, in connection with or arising out of or relating to:</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">11.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">any differential stamp duty obligations in case this Agreement or any other Finance Document is received in a state other than the state where it is executed;</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">11.3.</div>
      <div class="txt">providing the Loan Facility and any amounts thereunder;</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">11.4.</div>
      <div class="txt">any instructions received by the Lender, which it believes in good faith to be instructions provided by fax or by e-mail from the Borrower or an authorised representative of the Borrower;</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">11.5.</div>
      <div class="txt">any breach by the Borrower or the Co-Borrower of any of the terms and conditions of this Agreement and Finance Documents;</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">11.6.</div>
      <div class="txt">any liability including third-party liability that may arise out of the possession, operation and use of the Vehicle by the Borrower or by any of its employees or agents or by any other persons whosoever whether or not authorized by the Borrower for use of the said Vehicle and incidental to that purpose;</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">11.7.</div>
      <div class="txt">any claims, losses, demands, actions, costs, expenses and liabilities incurred or suffered by the Lender by reason of the Vehicle not being free from encumbrance and/or any previous charge;</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">11.8.</div>
      <div class="txt">the occurrence of the Event of Default;</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ================= PAGE 6 ================= -->
  <div class="page">
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">11.12.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Lender shall not in any way be liable or responsible for any delay, omission or neglect in encashment, damage or loss of any Payment Instruments including PDCs/cheques (already given or to be given by the Borrower(s) to the Lender in terms hereof) for any reasons whatsoever, and /or no interest or compensation shall be payable by the Lender to the Borrower on the proceeds held/to be held by the Lender.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">11.12.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Lender shall not be responsible for delay, or non-delivery, or any defect, damage, or quality of the Vehicle, for which the Borrower shall be solely responsible. It is further agreed that the Lender shall not be responsible or liable even if there is a defect or dispute of any nature in the title (even if the Vehicle is found to be a stolen Vehicle) or ownership of the Vehicle and that the Borrower shall be responsible to independently satisfy itself in this regard.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-heading">12. SECURITY AND CONTRACTUAL COMFORT</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">12.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">In consideration of the Lender having granted or agreed to grant to the Borrower(s) the Loan Facility, the Borrower(s) hereby hypothecates and charges in favour of the Lender by creating a first and exclusive charge on the Vehicle for the due payment and repayment of the Loan Facility and the respective dues and hereby agrees to obtain an endorsement to that effect on the Registration Certificate from the concerned Authority. Provided that if the Vehicle (to be acquired) has not been delivered to and/ or registered (wherever applicable) in the name of the Borrower at the time of signing of this Agreement, the particulars of the Vehicle shall be informed in writing by the Borrower within 2 (two) calendar days of such delivery and/or registration, whereupon such writing shall form part of this Agreement and the Schedule hereto. The Lender shall be entitled to withhold disbursement of the whole or part of the Loan Facility until the submission of the above referred hypothecation certificate to the Lender by the Borrower(s); further without prejudice to any other rights available to the Lender hereunder or under law, the Lender may call upon the Borrower(s) to submit/procure such additional documents in original and/or assurance(s) as the Lender may require and the Borrower(s) hereby unconditionally and irrevocably agree(s) and undertake(s) to submit/procure such additional documents in original and/or assurance(s) to the Lender.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">12.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower and Co-Borrower agree that the Lender is not responsible for delivery of duly endorsed Registration Certificate and that the Borrower(s) shall not withhold payment of installments on the ground that Registration Certificate has not been delivered.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">12.3.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower(s) hereby expressly and irrevocably agree that they shall be estopped from taking the plea that on the date this Agreement was signed the exact details of the Vehicle were not available.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">12.4.</div>
