    <div class="section-heading">23. SEVERABILITY & ILLEGALITY</div>

    <p>If, at any time, any provision of this Agreement is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable in any respect, the legality,
      validity or enforceability of the remaining provisions will not, in any way, be affected or impaired.</p>

    <p>If it becomes unlawful in any applicable jurisdiction for the Lender to perform any of its obligations as contemplated by this
      Agreement or any other Finance Document, the Lender shall promptly notify the Borrower upon becoming aware of that event
      and in which case the Facility, or a part thereof shall stand cancelled, and the Borrower shall repay the same forthwith to the
      Lender.</p>

    <div class="section-heading">24. GRIEVANCE REDRESSAL</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">24.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">The Borrower may register a complaint with the Lender with respect to the Loan Facility, at info@satinfinserv.com. The Borrower may also correspond with the Company at the below mentioned address: Customer Service Department, Plot no &ndash; 492, 4th floor 'B' wing, Udyog Vihar Phase III Gurugram, Haryana 122016.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">24.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">If the Borrower is not satisfied with the resolution received from above channels, or if the customer does not receive a response from the Lender in 7 (seven) calendar days, the customer may write to the Designated Officer or the Principal Nodal Officer. The Principal Nodal Officer shall be responsible for receiving and managing grievances at clientgrievance@satinfinserv.com.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">24.3.</div>
      <div class="txt">If the Borrower is not satisfied with the response from the 2nd level of escalation, then the Borrower may escalate the same with the concerned Banking Ombudsman/Ombudsman for NBFCs or the Customer Education and Protection Cell (CEPC) in RBI.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-heading">25. GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">25.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in all respects by the laws of India.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">25.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">Subject to Clause 26 (Arbitration), the Parties agree to submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts and tribunals of Delhi. The Borrower irrevocably submits to and accepts for itself and in respect of its property, generally and unconditionally, the jurisdiction of these courts and tribunals, and irrevocably waives any objection now or in future, to the laying of the venue of any proceedings in the courts or tribunals of Delhi and any claim that any such proceedings have been brought in an inconvenient forum. The submission to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Delhi is for the benefit of the Lender only and will not (and will not be construed so as to) limit the right of the Lender to take proceedings in any other court of competent jurisdiction, nor shall the taking of proceedings by the Lender in any one or more jurisdictions preclude the taking of proceedings by the Lender in any other jurisdiction (whether concurrently or not) if and to the extent permitted by Applicable Law.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-heading">26. ARBITRATION</div>

    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">26.1.</div>
      <div class="txt">Any dispute, difference, controversy or claim arising out of or in connection with this Agreement and/or the relationship between the Parties, including any dispute relating to the interpretation, construction, validity, enforceability, performance or breach of this Agreement, shall be referred to and finally resolved by arbitration in accordance with the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, as amended from time to time, and applicable law.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="clause">
      <div class="num wide">26.2.</div>
      <div class="txt">The arbitration shall be conducted by a sole arbitrator to be appointed in accordance with the provisions of this Clause. The Lender shall issue a written notice to the Borrower proposing a panel of not less than three independent and eligible arbitrators, each of whom shall be eligible under the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996 and not ineligible under Section 12 (5) read with the Seventh Schedule thereto. Within five Business Days from receipt of such notice, the Borrower shall select and communicate to the Lender the name of any one arbitrator from the proposed panel. In the event the Borrower fails to communicate its selection within</div>
    </div>
  </div>

